        <h3>Jonathan Glass - the Artist</h3>
        <p>
          Jonathan took pastel and figurative studies from ages 10-18. He considers his passion to have started in his third year of college. Teacher Alan E. Cober taught journaling of experiences through sketchbook class. This was informative to develop his personal style of drawing. Jonathan also invested a lot of time getting to know elderly people in the old homes of Amherst NY. This was around the time his grandfather was dying. Although not limited to a theme, Alan E Cober encouraged Jonathan to draw in anatomy labs, baseball games, grade school, zoos and (his favorite), concerts.
